CSS- Cascading Style Sheets

CSS rules
1. Selector
2.Declaration block{}

p{
    property : value;
    color : blue
    font-size : 16px;
}

Selectors:

1. Universal selector (*) -targets all elements
*{
    ...style goes here
}

2. Element selector - target specific elements
h1 {
    color : purple;
    font-size : 16px;
}

3. class selector - targets elements with a specific class attribute (.)